Progress Report paccmann_gp¶

Aim of project: use Bayesian Optimisation with GP processes to optimise the sampling of the SVAE latent space in order to generate smiles which are optimised for specific criteria.

Week 1 summary:

  • Created a minimization function for the following criteria: target molecular weight, SA score and QED
  • Poor results (see below for optimisation for MW close to 100 and for MW close to 700)

  • Assessed if changing sampling method improved results (change the temperature value of the samplingsearch)
  • No drastic improvement by changing sampling method

Week 2 summary:

  • Adjusted the code to sample a batch of smiles for each latent point during the optimisation process
  • Studied the effect of evaluating a batch of smiles instead of a single smile for each latent point assessed during the optimisation process
  • Evaluating a batch of 30 smiles per latent point leads to a substantially better optimisation
  • Studied the effect of increased the number of points evaluated to n_calls=200 (increased eval condition)

Week 3 summary:

  • Studied Affinity optimisation

  • Created a combined minimisation function: worked for affinity but not qed

  • Studied the effect of optimising for a combination of different criteria scaled with different ratios
  • Did not work for the QED optimisation due to code error which led to qed minimisation being ignored

Week 4 summary:

  • Fixed code to enable the optimisation for a combination of different criteria
  • Continued studying the effect of optimising for a combination of different criteria
  • The results are encouraging but it appears that a large value of n_calls is required

Appendix - Week 1¶

Files created:

  • Environment (conda.yml)
  • Generator file/class (smiles_generator.py): created valid smiles from latent represention
  • Optimization file/class (gp_optimizer.py): GP optimization
  • Minimization function for MW (mw_minization.py): minimize abs(target-MW)
  • Minimization function for SA (sa_minization.py): minimize sa_score
  • Minimization function for QED (qed_minization.py): minimize 1-qed

Evaluation method:

  • Select 10 points in latent space (randomly or through optimisation)
  • For each point generate 25 smiles structures
  • Analyse distribution of e.g. MW of points and shift in median

Testing:

  • basic conditions: MW minization with two target MW + SA optimization

params=dict(dimensions=[(-5.0, 5.0)]*256, acq_func="EI", n_calls=100, n_initial_points=20, initial_point_generator='random', random_state=1234)

  • Increase n_calls to 150
  • Tried changing Temperature
  • Tried different search methods to generate smiles

def file_loading_format_mw_qed_sa(files):
    molecular_weights=[]
    qed_scores=[]
    sa_scores=[]
    for file in files:
        with open(file, 'r') as f:
            f.readline()
            for line in f:
                row = line.split()
                molecular_weights.append(float(row[1]))
                qed_scores.append(float(row[2]))
                sa_scores.append(float(row[3]))
    return molecular_weights, qed_scores, sa_scores

QED

".../site-packages/rdkit/Chem/QED.py", line 245, in properties mol = Chem.RemoveHs(mol)

SA

File ".../paccmann_generator/drug_evaluators/sas.py", line 74, in sa_score score1 /= nf ZeroDivisionError: float division by zero

Optimization process

RecursionError: maximum recursion depth exceeded (when T is very low)

Observations:

  1. Smiles generator has to loop a lot as many smiles outputs are not valid --> Slow optimisation
  2. Often distributions of MW/SA/QED for different points have same wide distribution with same median --> so optimsation tricky
  3. Might need to check which molecules get discarded could affect MW distribution

def file_loading_format_index_mw_qed_sa(files):
    smiles_index = []
    molecular_weights = []
    qed_scores = []
    sa_scores = []
    point_index = []
    p_i = 0
    for file in files:
        p_i+=1
        with open(file, 'r') as f:
            f.readline()
            for line in f:
                row = line.split()
                smiles_index.append(float(row[0]))
                molecular_weights.append(float(row[1]))
                qed_scores.append(float(row[2]))
                sa_scores.append(float(row[3]))
                point_index.append(p_i)
    return point_index, smiles_index, molecular_weights, qed_scores, sa_scores

def file_loading_format_affinity(files):
    smiles_index=[]
    affinity=[]
    point_index=[]
    p_i=0
    for file in files:
        p_i+=1
        with open(file, 'r') as f:
            f.readline()
            for line in f:
                row = line.split()
                smiles_index.append(float(row[0]))
                affinity.append(float(row[1]))
                point_index.append(p_i)
    return point_index, smiles_index, affinity
In [188]:
def file_loading_format_affinity_qed(files):
    smiles_index=[]
    affinity=[]
    qed_scores=[]
    point_index=[]
    p_i=0
    for file in files:
        p_i+=1
        with open(file, 'r') as f:
            f.readline()
            for line in f:
                row = line.split()
                smiles_index.append(float(row[0]))
                affinity.append(float(row[1]))
                qed_scores.append(float(row[2]))
                point_index.append(p_i)
    return point_index, smiles_index, affinity, qed_scores

def file_loading_format_affinity_qed_sa(files):
    smiles_index=[]
    affinity=[]
    qed_scores=[]
    sa_scores=[]
    point_index=[]
    p_i=0
    for file in files:
        p_i+=1
        with open(file, 'r') as f:
            f.readline()
            for line in f:
                row = line.split()
                smiles_index.append(float(row[0]))
                affinity.append(float(row[1]))
                qed_scores.append(float(row[2]))
                sa_scores.append(float(row[3]))
                point_index.append(p_i)
    return point_index, smiles_index, affinity, qed_scores, sa_scores
